Tempo is typically expressed in BPM (beats per minute), and while it can be a whole number, it does not have to be. Decimal values can occur, especially in real-time applications where accuracy matters. For instance, using `toFixed(2)` allows you to display tempos like `120.25 BPM`. In practice, most musical tempos are rounded to whole numbers, but finer precision can be useful for certain applications.

